A fire turned a Swedish dance hall jammed with teen-age Halloween revelers into a deathtrap, killing at least 60 people and injuring about 180.
The fire was the deadliest in modern Swedish history since 1978, when 20 people died in the town of Boraas.
The Swedish news agency TT reported 190 people were taken to hospitals with injuries, and about 20 were in intensive care.
The fire, at the facilities of the Macedonian Association local immigrant group, was the deadliest in modern Swedish history.
The dance apparently was attended mostly by immigrants or children of immigrants.
